[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Spring Boot dependencies**\n\nI’m noticing that POM is missing the spring-boot-autoconfigure, which is needed at runtime for inspecting auto-configuration. It seems spring-boot-cache may depend on spring-boot properties but not on the autoconfigure condition. I wonder how CacheProperties can load at runtime without the autoconfigure classes if they are just simple POJOs. Covering auto-configuration requires extra dependencies, so I need to consider if I should add spring-boot-autoconfigure and spring-boot-test for proper setup. Let’s figure this out!\n\n**Assessing Spring Boot auto-configuration**\n\nI’ve noted that the jar contains autoconfigure classes marked with @AutoConfiguration, which are typically used in Spring Boot's cache auto-configuration. The ApplicationContextRunner, coming from spring-boot-test, relies on spring-boot-autoconfigure to function properly. However, I’m wondering if manually creating CacheProperties and CacheManagerCustomizers actually requires additional dependencies. I might need to check the documentation for Spring Boot caching and possibly look into the GitHub repository for build.gradle to examine test dependencies. Let’s dive in!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_05b832be528edd85016a3f5814611c8196b4fc6d00ac58d85e\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqP1gb8FDw5nemVvwktE9_OGDpVM2Jw8O_XskahDtYsBfvCnAtCQ6SSblkdZ9Q0cDqcMtE0zeAERv7PnXjjJnMYk9bKPmA14f7MmVpyp5h9zIIojsocGK8UxScCCU_BDSLW8CguLL9boLitZS7mE83vQiX2yz1L7w0W4y4GzkVsQUKdBVCtLWVDT8uGZTdt6gp6Uw_L82RbPy85KQyao2nnacjqzGsvLGXI1XVLHxB6GltgtVksNXDaPLkixMFxW38JZre2SCEgTGSMczhoeRe4Oi_ZpuJmtkEy149eqkkogvycux5grwMlsSGZ8eInwBYs1vG5CBCQHAcHfG-ZT-KfjixxCyAjSPtaog3uIj3CRGteHYjNULuuESLH7zOKcXBAgOyTSb3zqGk7rBvpRc0csGX89qySdrVdAjWxMSAVOyJK23nVMq9c3eCES4zoNe675kQt5wsqGGy9QfSMpJjRFcIY7cuMTQUtsralZC-mTtDuHkecG-xsMYmJLOpfaY8Y9GbdCD5A1-Iw7s9KGb4XK8T2