[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating dependencies for setup**\n\nI'm wondering if the deterministic setup should include certain dependencies like spring-boot-autoconfigure and spring-boot-test. I've noted that spring-boot-test is just a test helper. It seems like existing generated tests add spring-boot-test manually, and I need to ensure version coordinates match exactly. I’m also considering including the spring-boot-actuator-autoconfigure for loading specific configurations like CachesEndpointAutoConfiguration, but it raises questions about dependency coverage and whether too many options might complicate things.\n\n**Considering Spring Boot Dependencies**\n\nI'm looking into whether `autoconfigure:4.1.0` is an optional compile dependency. If I'm using `ApplicationContextRunner` from `spring-boot-test`, I wonder if it depends on autoconfigure transitively. It seems logical to check the POM of `spring-boot-test` to clarify this relationship. I want to make sure I'm getting the dependencies right for an effective setup! This could impact my project, so it's worth investigating more closely.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_05b832be528edd85016a3f581ec47c8196b681b907c2303555\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqP1gsV7U01bbBVk1aSho5Abc0rH5vtxpLOuKHadrc63uNGyaqs0EdlE3w74Xqfx1inNK76D6mvTUTlHlzKRTl5lTGcc2-1uiE3uwICtSxEcJi2-AY3dDt8cYT0h7XW2bpUa7bPTOa4uNPTxxEwT6gwErVtbrUtFyE4uwoEKkxPlIb8jTNDK6qQ7mcm7C0DDjfTpzDuGHcEBOaikroUzC5nLJZCHMc3BiVq1Dwn0zTSlxGtkeV9UeIGB_lpKdRxEEcwQWVAdPO83KNuzJpeSDh481fQkh37EUjoYvu8QxB4vz46iNZbgS-sbDbLAs7Qi8YYRMt3V3I-E4jUQdBG5Bsbv33JOYEy7LG7KYXpX1S3QUUAbRyhoq7n_qVvvozSiKiBly59LEhphZIBA9yN2AURZUeiEGKgwPNp3VIekVV_7JlQZxyuK0h0w7vTtQkRmAuB1VrHOfifV1EChpZ5oMZ-heXIaTVykP5UBwpqAAaz2ud5LPJ8ByQF0UHJg5FgzraG253RIvdgvwRbG_oukXgG6kZFspVvGmrNq0JkywG0EpgFdHt85H-8tfvIeBC-RXbLOTMx6cWKKRa3ZihiQAZQvV4IiEx6p6YpKMPp03UtECNUhJhOTLpRzysG8GOoi3sL4xleJF